# Agentic CV Pipeline System Rules
Whenever the user asks you to generate a CV, write an application, or work on this project:
1. You MUST immediately read `docs/AI_GENERATION_PROMPT.md` and follow its instructions strictly.
2. You MUST NOT generate standard free-form text CVs or hallucinate skills. 
3. If the user asks you to onboard their data, you MUST read `docs/AI_ONBOARDING_PROMPT.md` in its entirety BEFORE you begin. 
4. DO NOT create implementation plans for onboarding. Execute the data extraction and file updates directly.
5. Pay strict attention to the "CRITICAL EXCEPTIONS" (like mutually exclusive variants) and forbidden files (like `personal_dossier.md`) mentioned in the instructions.
6. NO GIT COMMANDS are allowed. Do not attempt to run `git` commands in the terminal.
